Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: vegascope
Version: 1.0.2
Summary: View Vega/Vega-Lite plots in your web browser from local or remote Python processes.
Home-page: https://github.com/diana-hep/vegascope
Author: Jim Pivarski (DIANA-HEP)
Author-email: pivarski@fnal.gov
License: BSD 3-clause
Download-URL: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/diana-hep/vegascope/master/vegascope.py
Description-Content-Type: UNKNOWN
Description: VegaScope is a minimal viewer of Vega and Vega-Lite graphics from Python. The Python process generating the graphics does not need to be on the same machine as the web browser viewing them.
        
        VegaScope has zero dependencies and can be installed as a single file.
        
        See `https://github.com/diana-hep/vegascope <https://github.com/diana-hep/vegascope>`_ for examples and help strings for documentation.
